PREFACE TO THE THIRD EDITION

BOTH Text, Analysis and Commentary in the Third Edition have been again subjected to a thorough revision. In the explanatory notes I have found it necessary to embody some sixty pages of new matter, while of the old compression here, expansion there, and, where superfluous or erroneous, excision has been employed unsparingly3 numerous fresh illustrations have been given and frequent reference has been made to the Grammars of Zumpt, Madvig, Draeger‚ Kennedy‚ Key and Roby.
